---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroText from '~/components/widgets/HeroText.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'The Execution-Cost Checklist — Model Real Fills Into Your Backtest',
  description:
    'A free, actionable checklist for day traders: the four fixes that turn a profitable backtest into a realistic one — model fills, work out break-even in ticks, measure your own stop slippage, and stop sizing up. The execution tax, made measurable.',
};

const fixes = [
  {
    n: '01',
    title: 'Model the fill the way reality does',
    points: [
      'A limit order counts as filled only if price trades THROUGH your level — not when it merely touches.',
      'Debit at least one tick of slippage on every market and stop order.',
      'Fill stops at the worst price of the bar, not the price you set.',
    ],
  },
  {
    n: '02',
    title: 'Work out your break-even in ticks',
    points: [
      'Break-even = commission ÷ tick value + 1 tick of spread you cross.',
      '≈ 1.5 ticks on the E-mini (ES) · ≈ 2.5 ticks on the micro (MES) — the micro costs more per tick because commission is a near-fixed dollar over a smaller tick.',
      'Subtract it from EVERY backtested trade, then re-plot the curve. That new curve is your real edge.',
    ],
  },
  {
    n: '03',
    title: 'Measure your own stop slippage',
    points: [
      'For your next 50 stopped-out trades, log: stop price − fill price.',
      'Fold the average into your costs — that is your real slippage distribution.',
      'Keep the $150 / 12-tick protection band in mind; on news and gaps, use a stop-LIMIT to cap how far you will fill.',
    ],
  },
  {
    n: '04',
    title: "Don't size your way back",
    points: [
      'A bigger order reaches deeper down the order book, so each extra contract fills a little worse than the last.',
      'Sizing up multiplies slippage — it cannot earn the cost back.',
      'Your one-lot backtest never charged you for this. Re-test at the size you actually trade.',
    ],
  },
];
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <HeroText
    title="The Execution-Cost Checklist"
    subtitle="Your strategy can win on paper and still lose live — because a backtest hands you three things the exchange never will. Here are the four fixes that make the gap measurable. Free, and yours to keep."
  />

  <!-- The four fixes -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 mb-14">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      {fixes.map((f) => (
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="shrink-0 inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-800 font-bold text-sm">{f.n}</span>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-3">{f.title}</h2>
              <ul class="space-y-2.5">
                {f.points.map((p) => (
                  <li class="flex gap-2.5 text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
                    <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-emerald-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
                    <span>{p}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="mt-6 text-xs text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed text-center">
      Once you account for these mechanical costs, any remaining gap between your corrected backtest and your live
      results is genuine behavior drift — the entries you jumped, the stops you widened, the size you reached for
      under pressure. That part you can measure straight from your broker's exported fills.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Soft product CTA -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-24">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-emerald-600/25 bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-emerald-50/30 p-7 shadow-md text-center">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-2">The mechanical tax you can model. The behavior, you can't feel.</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto mb-5">
        That leftover behavior drift is exactly what Meridian reads back to you — live, before you click. It runs
        every traditional risk limit, then adds the behavioral layer no limit can: it watches re-entry speed,
        stop manipulation and oversizing against your own baseline, and can step in before the order.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-7 py-3 rounded-full bg-emerald-600 text-white font-semibold transition-all hover:bg-emerald-700 text-sm">
          Start the 14-day free trial
        </a>
        <a href="/what-is-meridian-psi" class="text-sm text-emerald-700 font-medium hover:underline">How it works &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-zinc-400">NinjaTrader 8 · Tradovate &amp; Ironbeam (early access) — one license covers every platform.</p>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-6 text-center text-xs text-zinc-400">
      Educational only — not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
